00:52:50,202 --> 00:53:16,983
Renting rooms to lodgers is an important component of our naturally affordable housing supply. Since these rooms are often rented well below market rates, it can help to offset housing costs for lower income homeowners. The boundary between lodgers and other household members can be porous, as they may be care providers, friends or family, exchange students or guests for any length of time. Most importantly, having at least a decade of experience with guest household members who are typically working adults myself,

